# Swift iOS Game Studio (broad rule)

For any Swift / iOS / iPadOS **game** work in this repo, use the **swift-ios-game-studio**
skill. Canonical: `.agents/skills/swift-ios-game-studio/SKILL.md`
(Cursor copy: `.cursor/skills/swift-ios-game-studio/SKILL.md`).

It builds simple 2D games: coloring, puzzles, platformers, drag-and-drop, memory/matching,
lite runners, tap-reaction, educational mini-games.

## Always follow this workflow
1. Understand the request (genre, age, core verb, fail model, platforms/orientation).
2. Produce a one-page Mini-GDD (`assets/gdd-template.md`).
3. Choose mode: **SwiftUI-only** (static/turn-based), **SpriteKit** (motion/physics),
   or **hybrid** (`SpriteView` in a SwiftUI shell).
4. Define architecture (pure model + state machine + thin views).
5. Implement a small, polished MVP from the `assets/` templates.
6. Add unit tests for the model.
7. Build/test with `xcodebuild` when a project exists (see scripts).
8. Review child safety, privacy, accessibility, performance (`assets/review-checklist.md`).
9. Hand off: changed files, commands run + output, assumptions, risks.

## Non-negotiables
- No copyrighted assets — placeholder vector shapes / SF Symbols or user-owned assets only.
- Game rules in pure Swift (no SwiftUI/SpriteKit imports), unit-tested.
- Minimal dependencies (Apple frameworks preferred).
- Accessibility labels/values/traits on every interactive control; Dynamic Type; Reduce Motion.
- Kids apps: no tracking/analytics/ads/external-links/accounts; offline-first; no personal data;
  minimal permissions; parental gate for sensitive actions.
- Never claim guaranteed App Store / COPPA / Kids approval — give a checklist and risks.

When in doubt, apply documented defaults (ages 4–8, no-fail, both orientations, SwiftUI-only
unless physics is required) and write the assumptions into the Mini-GDD and handoff.

## Specialist roles (subagents)
For larger work, adopt one of the 12 specialist roles in `.cursor/rules/agents/` (or paste it as a
Custom Mode system prompt).
- Build: `game-coordinator` (decompose) → `game-designer` → `engine-architect` →
  `gameplay-programmer` (+ `narrative-writer`, `balance-economist`) → `qa-tester`.
- Review & audit (read-only): `code-reviewer` (diff/PR) + pre-release gate `code-auditor`,
  `security-auditor`, `performance-auditor`, `legal-compliance`.
Each role enforces the same contract above. Canonical specs: `.agents/agents/README.md`.
